Definition: marked by obliqueness or indirection in speech or conduct
Example: the explanation was circuitous and puzzling; a roundabout paragraph; hear in a roundabout way that her ex-husband was marrying her best friend
Synonyms: roundabout, marked, by, obliqueness, or, indirection, in, speech, conduct, the, explanation, was, and, puzzling, a, paragraph, hear, way, that, her, ex-husband, marrying, best, friend
Category: adj.all
